name: Zendesk Sell
description: Add a Zendesk Sell CRM Instance to connect your existing Zendesk Sell account to the CRM Hub, allowing you to manage contacts, leads, accounts, opportunities etc. across multiple CRM Elements. You will need your Zendesk Sell account information to add an instance.

configuration.name: Allow Select Fields parameter
configuration.description: Enables use of global fields query parameter to filter response to only specified fields. This will override any existing vendor functionality on the connector

configuration.name: Filter null values from the response
configuration.description: Used to enable/disable filtering of null values from the responses.

configuration.name: Default select fields
configuration.description: Generic map used to specify default fields for bulk download and GET /all requests. Each key should be the canonical objectName and values may be specified as a comma-delimited string or a list of strings

configuration.name: Callback Notification Signature Key
configuration.description: A key used to generate a validation hash header of the event/bulk notification webhook callback payload

resources.description: Find accounts in the CRM system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all accounts whose name contains the word smith, the search expression parameter will be where=name=smith. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 200 records will be returned. Only returns details about your account.

Find activities in the CRM system, using the provided CEQL search expression. The search expression in CEQL is the WHERE clause in a typical SQL query, but without the WHERE keyword. For example, to search for all activities whose name contains the word the search expression parameter will be where=name=jones. If a search expression is not provided, then the first 200 records will be returned.

parameters.name: page
parameters.description: The start page for pagination, which defaults to 1 if not supplied

parameters.name: pageSize
parameters.description: The page size for pagination, which defaults to 200 if not supplied

parameters.name: where
parameters.description: The CEQL search expression, or the where clause, without the WHERE keyword, in a typical SQL query. For example, to search for activities last modified on or after Jan 15, 2014, the search expression will be where: [lastModifiedDate=2014-01-15T00:00:00.000Z]. When this parameter is omitted, all activities are returned in a paginated fashion.

resources.description: Create a new activity in the CRM system. Activity creation will flow through Cloud Elements to your CRM service. With the exception of the [id] field, the required fields indicated in the activity model are those required to create a new activity. Required fields are the strings, [due_date] and [content].

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: The activity object to be created. With the exception of the [id] field, the required fields indicated in the activity model are those required to create a new activity. Required fields are the strings, [due_date] and [content].

resources.description: Delete an activity associated with a given ID from the CRM system.  Specifying an activity associated with a given ID that does not exist will result in an error message.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the activity to delete from the CRM system.

resources.description: Retrieve an activity associated with a given ID from the CRM system. Specifying an activity with a specified ID that does not exist will result in an error response.

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the activity to retrieve from the CRM system.

resources.description: Update the activity associated with the given ID in the CRM system. The update API uses the PATCH HTTP verb, so only those fields provided in the activity object will be updated, and those fields not provided will be left alone. Updating an activity with a specified ID that does not exist will result in an error response. Reads as a PUT

parameters.name: id
parameters.description: The ID of the activity to update in the CRM system.

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: The activity object, with those fields that are to be updated. Required fields are the strings, [due_date] and [content].
